			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you are setting and clearing interrupts 200+ times a frame, this may be the problem.<br /><br />Other games don't do this, which is why no emulator author has bothered to get the accuracy perfect on such a thing.<br /><br />MMC3 has a scanline counter system. I would use that. That just requires keeping interrupts ON the whole frame and just resetting a counter value several times a frame.<br /><br /><br />Also, are you using a PAL NES, diskover? That might be part of the issues that rainwarrior is having.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I will put the game on an MMC3 board</div> You might have issues, if the board doesn't have 4 screen mirroring, like the ROM.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
