					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The problem is that you did not disable APU Frame Counter IRQs at power on.  These are enabled by default, at least on NTSC consoles (and likely most emulators): <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/CPU_power_up_state">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/CPU_power_up_state</a><!-- m -->)<br /><br />Changing Mesen's code to boot with APU IRQs disabled fixes (almost) everything:<div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<a href="./download/file.php?id=13081&amp;mode=view"><img src="./download/file.php?id=13081&amp;t=1" alt="shadow.png" /></a><br />
			<span class="gensmall">shadow.png [ 25.98 KiB | Viewed 635 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div>I say almost because at some very specific character positions, the background (between the clouds &amp; ground) flashes in or out of existence for a few pixels.<br /><br />This issue reminds me of this problem bananmos had with a PAL rom: <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=214822#p214822">viewtopic.php?p=214822#p214822</a><!-- l --><br />It's possible that PAL NES might boot with the &quot;disable IRQ&quot; flag turned on for the frame counter, which would explain both issues. (I'm unsure if any of the PAL test roms check this particular behavior)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

